    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n381" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰτιάομαι</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἴτιος</span>), resolved forms constantly, inf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰτιάασθαι</span>, opt. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰτιόῳο, ῳτο</span>, ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ᾐτιάασθε, ἠτιόῳντο</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">accuse;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οἷον δή νυ θεοὺς βροτοὶ αἰτιόωνται</span>,
          ‘how mortals do bring charges against the gods!’ <i><span class="en">Od. 1.32</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
